#%PAM-1.0
# swaylock-effects PAM policy: password-first with fingerprint fallback.
#
# Verified against: pam_fprintd.c (MIN_TIMEOUT=10), pam_unix(8), swaylock-effects /etc/pam.d/swaylock package layout
# Reviewed: 2026-06-10
#
# DEVIATION: password is tried before fingerprint. PAM serializes both
# methods and swaylock does not render PAM info messages, so with the
# previous fingerprint-first order a typed password silently waited for
# the whole fingerprint window (2 tries x 10s = ~20s) before being
# checked. Effective flow now:
#   1. typed password -> pam_unix validates instantly (nodelay skips
#      the ~2s failure delay when the prompt is submitted empty).
#   2. empty prompt   -> pam_fprintd waits for a finger touch.
#   3. both failed    -> /etc/pam.d/login keeps the pam_faillock lockout.
#
# DEVIATION: a successful pam_unix unlock short-circuits the stack, so
# faillock's tally is not reset on success; it expires on its own
# (fail_interval, 15 min by default). Accepted trade-off for instant
# password unlocks.
#
# NOTE: pam_fprintd clamps timeout values below 10 up to MIN_TIMEOUT=10,
# so timeout=10 is the real minimum; lower values are cosmetic.

auth       sufficient   pam_unix.so try_first_pass nodelay
auth       sufficient   pam_fprintd.so max-tries=2 timeout=10
auth       include      login
